    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-06T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-06T21:00:00-05:00" n="637"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d637">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.79652/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-06T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >December 6, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2583. The Department believes, in answer to 3498, November 29, 4 p.m.<note n="65"
                        xml:id="d637fn65">Not printed.</note> that it might be advisable for you to
                    inform your British colleague that Spain has granted us temporary landing rights
                    for American commercial airlines. You might add that this was on a basis
                    entirely separate and apart from the question of aviation gasoline; that we hope
                    to begin a token service in the near future on a limited basis; and that we are
                    beginning to work out plans looking to a service which possibly may transit
                    Spain. It might also be <pb facs="0723" n="711" xml:id="pg_711"/> advisable to
                    point out to him that because of Spain’s neutrality we were naturally required
                    to stress the commercial aspect of the service.</p>
                <p>The Department will give corresponding advice to the British Embassy here.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
